-- Power Plant Builder Tecpro Systems Rises as Much as 28% in Mumbai Debut
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2010-10-12T08:50:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/tecpro-systems-shares-gain-as-much-as-20-percent-in-mumbai-trading-debut.html
Tecpro Systems Ltd. , an Indian
engineering company, surged as much as 28 percent on its trading
debut in Mumbai after investors demanded 24.4 times the stock on
sale in its initial public offer last month.  The shares, which  listed   at 425 rupees, climbed to 454.25
rupees in Mumbai. They changed hands at 423 rupees at 1:23 p.m.
The company sold 6.25 million shares and an investor Metmin
Investments Holdings Ltd. sold 1.3 million shares at 355 rupees
each to raise a total 2.68 billion rupees.  Tecpro, based in New Delhi, is an engineering, procurement
and construction company that builds bulk material handling
systems, captive power plants and pollution control systems for
clients such as  Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltd. , NTPC Ltd.,
Reliance Infrastructure Ltd. and ACC Ltd.  Tecpro has an order backlog of 23 billion rupees, Chairman
 Ajay Kumar Bishnoi  said in Mumbai today. Sales may grow as much
as 40 percent in the year ending March 31, he said.  Tecproâ€™s profit and sales doubled last year, according to
its sale document.  To contact the reporter on this story:
